The thesis of the APEC Center’s paper: At the current moment in world’s history there is a growth of Russia’s “Pax Rusa” desire and expanding new historical era called “The AshkaNaZi world” is defined by Russia, a development that creates alarming prerequisites for sharp and systemic destabilization of the entire civilized world. Russia’s actions is Russia’s real perception of her own history and its impact on the international policy in all continents of the globe. In fact, a definite Russia’s experience in restructuring the geopolitical processes in Eurasia, European, Near and Mideastern firmly determines in advance Russia’s actions in the coming years and decades. This imperial experience in order to serve Russia’s interests reveals indisputable future occupation specter of the whole world under “Pax Rusa” and this “Imperial experience” is historically proves its unwavering loyalty to the interests and achievements of Russia. Since then the historical experience of Russia proves that Russia’s imperial desire is based on her relationship with most of European countries, a danger that has grown by means of new programs and renewed unilateral imperial structure, and will have a direct impact on the Eurasian states in the near future.
